title: Painted Lion Façade Coaster
description:
Coaster developed from Edward Kemeys’ Lions, 1893 and main entrance, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Even larger cups will fit well, and the cork bottom protects surfaces. Featuring an oil painting of the front of the museum with the Lions, 1893, by Edward Kemeys.

  • Dimensions: 4.25 x 4.25 in.
  • Material: Ceramic, cork bottom.
  • Wipe with damp cloth.
